main event: A UFO was visually observed by military personnel on October 24, 1964 at 0130Z near the coordinates 66.00N 27.40W.
interesting points: The object was observed contrary to the normal satellite path, but was evaluated as a satellite.
The object's course was 270 degrees and its speed and altitude were unknown.
The sighting was reported through military channels, including the Commander in Chief of the Atlantic Fleet and the Continental Air Defense Command.
The report states that there was insufficient data to fully evaluate the sighting.
Advance copies of the report were delivered to the Defense Intelligence Agency and the National Interpretation Network.
